<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Comic Sans MS,Arial, Helvetica, Geneva" SIZE="+" color=cc9900>
<h2>Homework suggestions</h2>
</font>

<ul>
<li>January
<ol>
<li>Summarize one of the proofs that the mapping class group is generated by Dehn twists
<li>Find a minimal generating set for the mapping class group of a punctured surface
<li>Perform the euclidean algorithm for curves with several specific elements of H_1(S<sub>g</sub>;Z)
<li>Determine which pairs of vectors v and w satisfy t<sub>v+w</sub>=t<sub>v</sub>+t<sub>w</sub>
<li>What is the analogue of the symlpectic group for a surface with boundary?
<li>Classify bounding pair maps up to conjugacy in the Torelli group
<li>Complete the third proof that the Torelli group is torsion free
<li>Construct n-gons in the complex of cycles.  Which integral polygons can be realized? <a href=polygons.pdf>Solution by Tao Yu</a>
</ol>
</ul>

<ul>
<li>February
<ol>
<li>Complete one of the 5 calculations required to complete Johnson I.
<li>Explain the Rochlin invariant.
<li>Show that the BCJ maps are homomorphisms.
<li>Compute the image of a BP map under a BCJ map.
<li>Find generators for the kernel of the Chillingworth map.
<li>Exposit Irmer's paper. <a href=irmer.pdf>Exposition and new proof by Tao Yu</a>
<li>Exposit Moriyama's paper for the case n=2.
</ol>
</ul>

<ul>
<li>March / April
<ol>
<li>Explain Morita's argument for the image of handlebody Torelli under Johnson
<li>Check that last relation in Johnson II, to show that K/T is abelian
<li>Explain (part of) Gaifullin's new paper on the homology of Torelli
<li>Explain the definition of the Casson invariant for a 3-manifold
<li>Prove that the abelianization is generated by twists of genus one
<li>Explain Irmer's theorem that Torelli monodromies for fibered 3-manifolds are unique
<li>Prove the BNS theorem
<li>Relate the BNS invariant to actions on R-trees
<li>Explain the proof of the general result of Church-Ershov-Putman
<li>Prove that K is finitely generated without the Zariski topology
<li>Explain why the cohomological dimension of Torelli is 3g-5
</ol>
</ul>


